window.bookSummaryJSON = "Two-time Spur Award nominee Cameron Judd spins Westerns that lasso listeners' attention. In this inspiring story of self-sacrifice, menacing dangers spur 17-year-old Pennington Malone to grow up quickly. With his father in Leavenworth Prison, Penn travels to Dodge City packing his dad's loaded six-gun. He soon meets Jonah Littlejohn, a lanky man gifted with incredible strength and boxing prowess - and haunted by painful secrets. But when Penn learns that three shadowy riders are trailing him, and framing him for murders they committed, he needs all the help he can get."; 
